Johannesburg Metro Police are urging motorists to make alterative plans in the interim. JOHANNESBURG The Randburg Licensing Department has been closed for the day due to a damaged water pipe.Johannesburg Metro Police are urging motorists to make alternative plans in the interim.Last month, this same station was affected when some staff members were suspended for alleged corruption.Metro Police s Wayne Minnaar says: Randburg Licensing offices will remain closed today because of the damaged water pipe and as a result there s no water to the Randburg Civil Centre. The public can renew vehicle disc at Roodepoort, Midrand, Sandton and Langlaagte Licensing offices for today. 